{
  "stem": "17044.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 262.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He paid for our boarding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remember, was a doctor, good man, took us in to give us the first meal.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had soup.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But I didn't have soap for-- for two, three years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Was like manna.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were-- I were in-- and this was under Romanian occupied place, where they call this Transnistria.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Transnistria-- I didn't know what Transnistria means until I came to United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I know-- I learned-- in the United States, I learned 'trans' means the other side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a river, Dniester, after Romania. it was the border between Russia and Romania.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "This part, where they gave it to the Romanians, they called it Transnistria.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "[INTERPOSING VOICES] So call this part 'the other side of the Dniester, [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was labor camps there, people starving, dying, day and night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And, I was in this ghetto until a certain time, and then the ghetto couldn't pay for me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So I had-- in the place where I was staying, was a guy, was a pocket-picker.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So if I was babysitting for the children, and he used to give me a piece of bread.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then once they grabbed people for work, for a lager, labor lager.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it's a native in the same town-- he had money to buy himself out with gold.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So we have to fill in the 300 people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So they came, and the place where we're staying is a bathhouse.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But I-- I hid myself in a kettle, and the people wouldn't give me out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But the police wouldn't give out-- they knew I'm there.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They knew me, because I'm-- I'm a refugee.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they're looking for me to take the place for the other guy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They wouldn't give up.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
